metadata.title: Can a user open an account in various devices at the same time?
metadata.docs: No, a user can log into his/her account in one device only at a time.

metadata.title: Can I have multiple accounts through the same phone number?
metadata.docs: No, you cannot because a phone number is uniquely identified with an account.

metadata.title: Can I pause my account with FamPay?
metadata.docs: You can pause your IDFC FIRST Bank-Fampay Prepaid Card so that no transactions are enabled through it.

metadata.title: Is there an offline method for getting the KYC done?
metadata.docs: Our KYC verification procedures are conducted online.

metadata.title: My KYC request got rejected.
metadata.docs: If your KYC request gets rejected, then you are eligible for a min-KYC procedure.

metadata.title: Does every user have to get the KYC done?
metadata.docs: Yes, it is mandatory for every IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPay user to get the KYC done as per regulatory guidelines. Please follow the steps on the IDFC FIRST Bank FamPay application to complete the KYC.

metadata.title: What are the documents required for KYC?
metadata.docs: KYC can be easily processed using any of the following documents of the user-, Voter ID, Passport, Driving License or PAN Card or any other government issued ID

metadata.title: What are the limits for a minimum KYC account?
metadata.docs:
With a minimum KYC you can: 
- Transact upto INR 10,000 per month 
- Transact upto INR 1,00,000 per year 
- Cannot do P2P transfers

metadata.title: What are the limits for an Full KYC account?
metadata.docs:
With an Full KYC account, you can: 
- Transact upto INR 1,00,000 per month 
- Transact upto INR 2,00,000 per year 
- Can perform P2P transfers

metadata.title: Where can I use IDFC FIRST Bank - Fampay Prepaid Card ?
metadata.docs: IDFC FIRST Bank - Fampay Prepaid Card can be used at any merchant (POS & ECOM) who accepts Rupay cards.

metadata.title: How to use IDFC FIRST Bank - Fampay Prepaid Card for online purchases?
metadata.docs: You can find your card on the home screen. On swiping down, you get the details of the card which can be used on all the online platforms for purchases. Tap on the card number to copy it and paste wherever you want to spend.

metadata.title: What is the Pin for the card?
metadata.docs: Pin for the card is kept for your security. Please do not share or forget this. Pin will be used for authentication of payments when you swipe the IDFC FIRST Bank - Fampay Prepaid Card offline.

metadata.title: Can I pause or block my card?
metadata.docs: Yes, you can do it on your fingertips using the app whenever you feel like it. While blocking your card will discard your card permanently, pausing will deactivate your card until you resume it. No transactions will be processed when the card is deactivated.

metadata.title: Why is there no number on the physical card?
metadata.docs: Because it is much more secure in case someone else gets the card. You can get the card details on the app which can be used for online purchases.

metadata.title: How to order a physical card?
metadata.docs: You can order the card from the app. Just go on the card screen, click on order card, fill in your details and we'll deliver it at your doorstep.

metadata.title: I lost my card. What do I do?
metadata.docs: You can block the card from the app anytime and apply for a new one.

metadata.title: How can I create a IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account?
metadata.docs: Post Creation of the family, adult in the family can create the IDFC FIRST Bank - Fampool account and becomes the owner of the account.

metadata.title: Can a minor add money?
metadata.docs: No, a minor can not add money. They can only request their parents to load the personal or FamPool account and receive money from others on FamPay.

metadata.title: Who can spend money from the IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account?
metadata.docs: The family members added by the KYCed adult owner to issue the add-on cards can use the FamPool account to spend.

metadata.title: How many members can be added in the IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account?
metadata.docs: Upto 2 minors can be added to the IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account to issue the add-on cards.

metadata.title: Can everyone view the transactions of IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account?
metadata.docs: The transactions that are made out of IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account can be viewed by all the members of FamPool account.

metadata.title: Can I transfer money from IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account to personal account?
metadata.docs: if you are a minor, then you need to request for the amount in the account and the owner will have to approve that amount.

metadata.title: I am a parent. How do I link my kid?
metadata.docs: Create your family on the app and invite your kid to it. Once your kid signs up and creates his profile on FamPay, he/she will need to accept the family invite and its done.

metadata.title: I am a kid. How do I request for money?
metadata.docs: Once your IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPool account is set, you can just go on your family and tap on "Request" --> Enter Amount --> Send request.

metadata.title: How can I transfer fund to someone who is not on IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPay?
metadata.docs: No, you cannot.

metadata.title: How can I add money to my IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPay account?
metadata.docs: The money can be added to your IDFC FIRST Bank - FamPay account through net banking, debit card and/or by using any UPI ID. We do not allow to load through cash or credit cards.

metadata.title: Every Little Thing Counts- Ways in Which You Can Contribute to Society as a Teenager💪🏽🧑‍🎓
metadata.docs: a few remarks should not overpower the hundreds and thousands of beneficiaries. Be consistent in your efforts.Learn from the realThere is a vast difference in the virtual world and the real dynamics of life. Reduce your social media time, and invest in talking to people in person, take a walk in the park, socialize (not on Instagram) or even join in a community activity! Best learnings come from your own experience.Does it really work?All this empowerment will help you as a teenager in molding your young creative minds and directing the abundant energy into the right cause. Ultimately, creating a better version of yourself with a more acceptable identity, empathetic approach to society, and reflective idealism. Where can I begin?Let’s see some of the most efficient and highly impactful habits that can change our world.Save waterSmall steps like turning off the tap while brushing/shaving, using a bucket and mug instead of showerheads for bath, channelling waste kitchen water into a garden can save several gallons of water – one of the scarcest resources on earth. Shortening of your bath for 5 minutes for a month can save ~3tn gallons of water in a lifetime.Save EnergyUse the natural daylight whenever possible; you can reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 0.15pound/hr. Breathe in the soothing calm breeze rather than the AC waves and switch off unnecessary light/fan when not required.Reduce your garbage dumpAvoid plastic bags and one-time usable cutlery. Did you know, India generates nearly 26,000 tonnes of plastic waste every day, making it the 15th biggest plastic polluter globally! Even a small NO to drinking straws and plastic stirrers can save several aquatic species. Invest in a reusable water bottle/coffee cup/portable cutlery.Save paper, save treesBeing GenZs, we have much more responsibility to conserve our resources for Gen Next, than ever before. Replace the needful with digital receipts/notifications and contribute enormously to paper conservation. Make the most of your notebook and write on both sides and on each line.Manage your financeIn today’s era, money has clearly overpowered every emotion and clarity. It’s time that you understand the value of the currency and the need to control the power which it drives. One simple way is to avail FamPay’s card! Easy to handle, mass usage, classy appearance, easy recharge options
